  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager/Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Managing &amp; Directing the assigned project resources to best meet project objective</li>\n  <li>Ensure all changes to specifications, work scopes, and drawings are properly documented</li>\n  <li>Efficient management of resources and materials</li>\n  <li>Responsible for project and site supervision, attend site meetings, coordination with sub-contractors, suppliers, consultants and clients and all scope of work that is require in the smooth implementation of a successful project development</li>\n  <li>Assist in resolving any issues or challenges that may arise during the project execution</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site inspections and quality control checks</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with safety regulations and industry standards</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with internal teams to ensure successful project delivery</li>\n  <li>Manage material at the construction site to ensure zero wastage and no overstock of material</li>\n  <li>Manage manpower and overtime costs to ensure optimal cost-benefit within or below budget</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and communicate with project teams, subcontractors, and suppliers</li>\n  <li>Ad hoc duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements: </strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of relevant experiences in Interior Fit-out Industry</li>\n  <li>Minimum higher NITEC/Diploma holders or candidates with relevant experience and proven track records will also be considered</li>\n  <li>Experience in Construction/Interior Design/Furniture Industry will be an added advantage</li>\n  <li>Able to start work within short notice preferred</li>\n</ul>",
